fields.value: Centro de Investigaciones Sobre la realidad Social (CIRES) [Spain], 1994 (M564V1)

authorName.value: Centro de Estudios sobre la Realidad Social

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The CIRES studies are conducted over a period of months in 1994. In 1994 the studies explore supranational identification, health, attitudes toward immigrants, culture as consumption, demands for social welfare, political and economic culture, orientation towards work, youth, and the environment. Studies are conducted under the supervision of Juan Diez Nicols.

Sample for all months: 1,200 persons of either sex, 18 years old and over, living in Spain. Random sample, stratified by autonomous regions and municipalities according to their size. Field Research: Conducted monthly from January to December, through personal interview at the interviewees' homes, by Redex Network (IOPE-ETMAR). Supervision by A.S.E.P of 20% of the interviews.
